---
description: Generate AI Editable HTML pages that can be locally edited by the browser extension.
globs: ["*.html"]
alwaysApply: false
---

When generating standalone HTML intended for local editing, use the `ai-editable-html-v1` protocol.

Requirements:

- Add `data-ai-editable-html="v1"` to the `<html>` element.
- Include one `<script id="ai-editable-html-model" type="application/json">` model.
- Add stable `data-edit-id` attributes to editable text elements.
- Add stable `data-flow-id` attributes to editable flow containers.
- Store flowchart nodes and edges in the JSON model.
- Use plain text labels and stable lower_snake_case IDs.
- Do not render editable flows only as static SVG or canvas.
- Include or inline the v1 runtime when the page contains flow blocks.
- Add the subtle GitHub badge unless the user asks for no branding.

Text block shape:

```json
{
  "id": "page_title",
  "type": "text",
  "selector": "[data-edit-id='page_title']",
  "content": "Editable title"
}
```

Flow block shape:

```json
{
  "id": "main_flow",
  "type": "flow",
  "selector": "[data-flow-id='main_flow']",
  "nodes": [
    { "id": "start", "label": "Start", "x": 40, "y": 80, "width": 140, "height": 56 }
  ],
  "edges": [
    { "id": "start_to_next", "source": "start", "target": "next", "label": "" }
  ]
}
```

Flow layout rules:

- Keep at least 48px gap between node bounding boxes.
- Never overlap nodes.
- Minimize edge crossings by separating branches into lanes or columns.
- Keep edge labels away from nodes.
- Use scrollable large canvases sized from node bounds instead of clipping.

If the project resources are installed, run this before returning HTML:

```bash
node .cursor/ai-editable-html/scripts/validate_editable_html.js path/to/page.html
```

Before returning HTML, verify that the model parses as JSON, selectors resolve, every edge references existing node IDs, and the validator has no errors.
